description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Senior Clinical Fellow in Acute Medicine (special interest posts) - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Chelsea, London&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting Registrar level opportunity for candidates who wish to obtain training and broaden their experience in Acute Medicine in a central London teaching hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a number of fellowship opportunities on offer which are detailed below but include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ambulatory Emergency Care &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Acute Medicine Senior Clinical Fellow&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Acute medicine &amp; cardiology clinical fellowship &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Acute medicine &amp; ultrasound clinical fellowship&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Acute medicine &amp; education fellowship&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Acute &amp; Emergency medicine fellowship&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Acute Medicine CESR programme&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will participate in a weekly rolling rota which will give you experience of our various Acute Assessment Unit (AAU) activities which include acute take, Ambulatory Emergency Care, and Enhanced Care. We also offer a generous amount of timeto develop a special skill or interest for a number of the fellowship jobs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The AAU at Chelsea is a high performing, vibrant and thriving training environment, with excellent levels of senior presence and support and a large and dedicated multi-professional team.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Charlotte Travill - Service Manager - Emergency &amp; Acute Medicine&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address charlotte.travill@chelwest.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 0203 315 2893&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details/informal visits please contact Dr Niki Mavroeidi (Consultant in Acute Medicine), Niki.Mavroeidi@chelwest.nhs.uk or Charlotte Travill (Service Manager), charlotte.travill@chelwest.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
